  "prompt": "How do you write a thesis statement on capital punishment?",
  "response": "Here are a few approaches to writing a thesis statement on capital punishment:\n\n1. Argumentative approach (against capital punishment):\n\"Capital punishment is an ineffective and morally unacceptable form of punishment that violates human rights and fails to deter crime effectively.\"\n\n2. Argumentative approach (in favor of capital punishment):\n\"Capital punishment serves as a necessary form of justice that provides closure for victims' families and acts as a significant deterrent to serious criminal behavior.\"\n\n3. Analytical approach:\n\"The debate surrounding capital punishment involves complex ethical, legal, and social considerations that challenge traditional notions of justice and human rights.\"\n\n4. Comparative approach:\n\"While capital punishment remains controversial, a comparative analysis of international legal systems reveals significant variations in its implementation and societal acceptance.\"\n\nWhen crafting your thesis statement, consider:\n- Your specific stance on the topic\n- The main points you'll discuss\n- The scope of your argument\n- Your evidence or reasoning\n\nTips for a strong thesis:\n- Be specific and clear\n- Take a definitive position\n- Provide a roadmap for your argument\n- Ensure it's arguable and not just a statement of fact\n\nChoose an approach that best matches your research and writing goals.",
